    <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>1/2 cup (1 stick) butter, room temp</li>
        <li>3/4 cup sugar</li>
        <li>2 eggs plus 1 tsp vanilla extract</li>
        <li>2 fresh bananas, mashed</li>
        <li>1/2 cup sour cream</li>
        <li>1 1/4 cup sweet rice flour or gluten-free flour blend</li>
        <li>1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp baking soda</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp salt</li>
        <li>1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Instructions:</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>
            Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Prepare a loaf pan by spraying the bottom and sides with nonstick cooking
            spray.
        </li>
        <li>In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar until smooth.</li>
        <li>Add eggs and vanilla extract, and beat until combined.</li>
        <li>Mix in mashed bananas and sour cream.</li>
        <li>In a separate bowl, whisk together gluten-free flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt.</li>
        <li>Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined.</li>
        <li>Stir in the chocolate chips.</li>
        <li>Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan. Sprinkle additional chocolate chips on top if desired.</li>
        <li>Bake for 35-50 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.</li>
        <li>Cool completely before cutting and serving.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Notes:</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>If your gluten-free flour blend already contains xanthan gum, you can omit it from the recipe.</li>
        <li>You can use regular baking cocoa if you don't have dark cocoa.</li>
        <li>
            If your loaf pan is too small, divide the batter between two pans and adjust baking time accordingly.
        </li>
        <li>You can use Greek yogurt instead of sour cream if preferred.</li>
    </ol>

